Hi everyone! It‚Äôs time for a quick update on the Curse of Strahd game:

There has been a huge outpouring of interest in doing this game on Nostr, which is amazing! When I first brought up this idea, it basically fell flat and got no attention, so I‚Äôm very happy to see such a large number of people interested!

Table space is limited - it is really only possible to handle 4-6 people effectively as players, especially with so many being new. I‚Äôve been getting schedule information from everyone, and in the coming days, I‚Äôm going to post the day of the week and time that I will run the game here in this channel, based on my work schedule and which hours allow the most people to play, etc.

I am interested in finding out from the player base as well, if they specifically want this game to be ‚ÄúDungeons and Dragons‚Äù or if they would be interested in the game being run for Pathfinder 2E. For people who have never played, it will make little difference, and to those who *have* played, it is a little more like D&D 3.5e, with some of the rougher corners knocked off.

Pathfinder has a history of being far kinder to small publishers, and makes *all* of their rule texts available for *free* here: https://2e.aonprd.com/

I also have over $100 in Pathfinder stuff for the Virtual Table Top we‚Äôre using, and can provide an even more immersive experience.

The game will *require* using a PC/Mac running an up to date version of Chrome, Edge, or Brave. WebGL simply does not play nice on Safari or FireFox. Linux users, we need to verify you can play before we start the game. Get with me in Nostr DMs to set up a time.

I know I‚Äôve been radio dark for a bit, but planning has been ongoing, and I‚Äôve been clearing some things off my plate to be ready to do this. I will host a nest this weekend (probably on Saturday) to do a final AMA and discuss the schedule. The schedule will be posted here at least a day before hand. We will also discuss the table guidelines (mostly etiquette) that I enforce as a DM. Nothing woke or big brothery, just stuff that 12 years of DM‚Äôing has taught me makes the game run smoother and establishes flow. This will be important for all players, as every DM is a bit different, and we need to work together.

I am super honored to be able to be one of the first people to run a D&D-type game on Nostr. Thank you for allowing me to share a story with you, and I look forward to seeing you at the game.¬†
That's class man , thanks for the update. I personally would prefer 5e because that's what I have become used to , but if other people favor Pathfinder I'm not going to start a riot .
